definitions.definition: To summon (someone) with a subpoena (noun sense 1 ) to appear in court , or at a deposition or some other legal proceeding , as a witness to give testimony or to produce evidence ; to serve a subpoena on (someone).
To require (a document or other evidence) to be produced before a court, or at a deposition or some other legal proceeding.
To compel or summon (someone or something); to demand .

main_definition: ( law ) To summon (someone) with a subpoena (noun sense 1 ) to appear in court , or at a deposition or some other legal proceeding , as a witness to give testimony or to produce evidence ; to serve a subpoena on (someone).
secondary_definitions: ( law ) To require (a document or other evidence) to be produced before a court, or at a deposition or some other legal proceeding.
( figurative ) To compel or summon (someone or something); to demand .
